The article discusses a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump declaring October 18 to October 24, 2020, as National Character Counts Week. The proclamation recognizes everyday heroes and historical figures who have contributed to the freedom and well-being of the nation. It highlights the selfless acts of kindness and sacrifice displayed by individuals in various fields such as the Armed Forces, law enforcement, first responders, community volunteers, faith organizations, teachers, mentors, and family members. The article also acknowledges the importance of moral character, especially during the ongoing coronavirus pandemic, and encourages Americans to show compassion, kindness, and virtue towards others. The proclamation calls upon public officials, educators, parents, students, and all Americans to observe the week with appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs.